      "url": "https://www.epanorama.net/documents/video/phosphor_decay.html",
      "retrieved_at": "2026-05-26",
      "notes": "B&W televisions of the era used P4 phosphor (bluish-white with cool color point ~565/540 nm component mix). No shadow mask. Aggressive screen curvature characteristic of pre-1980 TVs."
